# Derived from llama3.1:8b with an enlarged context window, for the PageIndex
# retrieval experiment (IDX-O index generation and RET-OLL retrieval).
#
# WHY: The IDX-D structure dump the retriever must read is ~9,000 tokens (IDX-C is
# larger, since summaries inflate the tree). Ollama's DEFAULT context window is only
# ~2K-4K tokens regardless of what the model architecture supports, so the retriever
# would silently see a TRUNCATED index and navigate blind. 32768 comfortably fits the
# structure dump + fetched page content + the tool-calling conversation. llama3.1
# supports up to 128K if you need more; larger num_ctx uses more RAM (~8B model at
# 32K ≈ several GB), so tune to your machine.
#
# BUILD (required once per machine — a fresh clone / new machine will NOT have this
# model until you run this):
#   ollama create llama3.1-8b-ctx32k -f config/ollama/llama3.1-8b-ctx32k.Modelfile
#
# USE:
#   retriever (RET-OLL):     ollama_chat/llama3.1-8b-ctx32k   (ollama_chat = tool-calling path)
#   index model (IDX-O):     ollama/llama3.1-8b-ctx32k
FROM llama3.1:8b
PARAMETER num_ctx 32768
